I have no idea how they've come to the conclusion that producing and airing the plethora of suckfest movies that they do is a good/money-making decision.

That network has been nothing but worthless useless garbage since they canceled Farscape.
Battlestar Galactica and Stargate are such fail goddamn shows.
Merlin is the only decent thing they have going for them and I watch it when it's new, not two years old.
All inclusive, taking all that into account, this is still the best one of their suckfest movies I've seen in 5 years and I'm hoping that it portends well for their future but have very low expectations.
